<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 7: VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN
        BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - REAR OIL SEAL AND WEAR SLEEVE - REAR OIL SEAL AND WEAR SLEEVE INSTALLATION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>REAR OIL SEAL AND WEAR SLEEVE INSTALLATION</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Flywheel Housing Installed</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>INSTALL THE REAR OIL SEAL AND WEAR SLEEVE AS A UNIT. DO NOT REMOVE THE SEAL FROM THE WEAR
                        SLEEVE PRIOR TO INSTALLATION.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>Install a new rear oil seal and crankshaft wear sleeve assembly using installer tool
                <emph type="bold">ZTSE4374b</emph>
                as follows:
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean crankshaft flange and seal carrier bore thoroughly. Remove any debris.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach rear oil seal/wear sleeve guide to crankshaft flange and secure with two (2)
                    mounting screws (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600713">7.13</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Coat inner I.D. of wear sleeve and O.D. of oil seal with Aviation Permatex #3 (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600714">7.14</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position oil seal and wear sleeve over crankshaft.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Proper use of installer tool will assure that seal and wear sleeve are pressed onto the
                            crankshaft flange to the proper depth.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble rear oil seal/wear sleeve installer tool onto crankshaft. Using a wrench, turn
                    forcing nut on installer tool until seal and sleeve are seated in the bore (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600715">7.15</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove oil seal/wear sleeve installation tool.</para>
                <figure id="ef1600713" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5174" filename="../figeg5/eg5174.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.13 Installing Rear Oil Seal Installer Tool</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600714" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5178" filename="../figeg5/eg5178.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.14 Preparing Rear Oil Seal</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600715" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5180" filename="../figeg5/eg5180.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.15 Installing Rear Oil Seal</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
